{
  "texts": [
    "All other models use 4bit GPTQ, which is much faster.",
    "Recently, the usage of LLMs as a judge for evaluation of language models has become the de facto standard, since it seems to offer a good balance between semantically correct evaluation of answers to open-ended questions and manual effort.",
    "Most of the time, GPT-4 is used [49], but lately specialized language models are proposed as alternatives [50], [51], [52].",
    "We included results of automatic evaluation from JudgeLM and Auto-J.",
    "They rated model answers against each other, and we calculated an Elo-rating from these results (see Table 5)."
  ]
}